content.text:
The issue was that `SharedFlow.toList(destination)` and `SharedFlow.toSet(destination)` were implemented by delegating to `(this as Flow).toList()` and `(this as Flow).toSet()` respectively, ignoring the passed `destination` argument. This caused the method to always return a new collection instead of populating the provided one.

The fix involves updating `kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/src/flow/operators/Lint.kt` to pass the `destination` parameter to the delegate calls.

I have verified the fix with a regression test.

```kotlin
// kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/src/flow/operators/Lint.kt

public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toList(destination: MutableList<T> = ArrayList()): List<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toList(destination) // Changed from (this as Flow<T>).toList()

// ...

public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toSet(destination: MutableSet<T> = LinkedHashSet()): Set<T> =
    (this as Flow<T>).toSet(destination) // Changed from (this as Flow<T>).toSet()
```

